<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
Blconf-GObject Binding

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
Functions to bind Blconf properties to GObject properties

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
Often it may be useful to bind an Blconf property to a GObject property.
Settings dialogs often display the current value of an Blconf property,
and a user may edit the value to change the value in the Blconf store.
If the Blconf property changes outside the settings dialog, the user will
usually want to see the settings dialog automatically update to reflect
the new value.

With a single line of code, Blconf's binding functionality can automate
all this.
</para>

